TASK SPECIFICATION

Task ID

TASK-20260628-0008

---

Task Name

GitHub Repository Messaging System

---

Assigned To

Task Manager

---

Priority

Critical

---

Objective

Design and implement a repository-based messaging system that enables AI agents to communicate asynchronously through GitHub without direct communication channels.

The Task Manager is responsible for planning, dividing the project into implementation tasks, assigning those tasks to available agents, supervising execution, verifying deliverables, and integrating the final messaging system.

---

Scope

Create a complete messaging framework including:

- Repository message architecture
- Message lifecycle
- Message specification
- Directory structure
- Message routing
- Broadcast messages
- Direct messages
- Task notifications
- Status updates
- Reply mechanism
- Message archival
- Cleanup policy
- Security validation

---

Task Manager Responsibilities

Phase 1 — Analysis

- Review existing AIOS specifications.
- Determine how the messaging system integrates with:
  - WORKFLOW.md
  - COORDINATION.md
  - AGENT_SPEC.md
  - TASK_SPEC.md
  - REPORT_SPEC.md
  - SECURITY.md

---

Phase 2 — Planning

Design the complete messaging architecture.

Define:

- Directory layout
- Message format
- Naming conventions
- Lifecycle
- Read/write permissions
- Security rules
- Synchronization workflow

---

Phase 3 — Task Assignment

Divide the project into independent implementation tasks.

Assign work to available agents based on capability and current workload.

Do not assign duplicate work.

Do not reference specific agent names in task definitions.

Possible work packages include:

- Message specification
- Directory implementation
- Send/receive workflow
- Broadcast mechanism
- Reply mechanism
- Archive system
- Cleanup automation
- Validation and testing
- Documentation

---

Phase 4 — Coordination

- Monitor implementation progress.
- Resolve conflicts.
- Verify deliverables.
- Merge compatible work.
- Reject incomplete implementations.
- Ensure compliance with AIOS specifications.

---

Phase 5 — Integration

After all implementation tasks are verified:

- Integrate all messaging components.
- Validate end-to-end communication.
- Update AIOS documentation.
- Submit the final implementation report.

---

Deliverables

- Repository Messaging System Architecture
- Message Specification
- Message Directory Structure
- Implementation Tasks
- Agent Assignment Report
- Verification Report
- Integration Report
- Updated AIOS Documentation
- Final Project Completion Report

---

Success Criteria

The task is complete only when:

- A fully functional GitHub repository messaging system is designed.
- Implementation tasks have been assigned without duplication.
- All assigned work has been verified.
- The messaging system integrates with existing AIOS specifications.
- Repository integrity and security are preserved.
- Final documentation and reports are completed.
